.TH lvsync 8
.SH NAME
\*Llvsync\*O \- Synchronizes logical volume mirrors that are stale in one or more logical volume
.SH SYNOPSIS 
.sS 
\*L/usr/sbin/lvsync\*O \*VLogicalVolumePath\*O ...\*O
.sE 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.iX "lvsync command"
.PP 
The \*Llvsync\*O command synchronizes the physical extents.
The physical extents are mirrors of the original physical extent that are stale
in the logical volume(s) specified by the
\*VLogicalVolumePath\*O parameter.  The synchronization process can be time
consuming, depending on the hardware characteristics and the amount of data.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
To synchronize the mirrors on logical volume lv05, enter:
.iS
lvsync /dev/vg01/lv05
.iE 
